{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643993","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643993"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:00:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:00:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18028"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18028","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18028"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10742"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78256"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10742"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18028"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63668"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25064"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25067"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26847"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78256","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78256"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the context of musculoskeletal pathology, certain conditions can lead to characteristic changes in bone structure visible on imaging studies. One of these conditions is characterised by intramedullary lytic \u0027punched out\u0027 lesions and diffuse osteopaenia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following fits this description?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Multiple myeloma","Osteosarcoma","Paget\u0027s disease of bone","Osteoporosis","Rheumatoid arthritis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMultiple myeloma\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by the presence of intramedullary lytic \u0027punched out\u0027 lesions and diffuse osteopaenia. These lesions result from increased osteoclastic activity, which is stimulated by factors produced by the myeloma cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteosarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E - Typically presents with a mixed lytic and sclerotic pattern, not \u0027punched out\u0027 lesions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaget\u0027s disease of bone\u003C/strong\u003E - Characterised by thickened, disorganised bone rather than lytic lesions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoporosis\u003C/strong\u003E - Leads to diffuse bone thinning but not \u0027punched out\u0027 lesions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERheumatoid arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily affects joints and may cause periarticular osteopenia, but not \u0027punched out\u0027 lesions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Multiple myeloma is characterised by intramedullary lytic \u0027punched out\u0027 lesions and diffuse osteopaenia on imaging.","The presence of these lesions is due to increased osteoclastic activity stimulated by myeloma cells."],"references":["Albagoush SA, Shumway C, Azevedo AM. Multiple Myeloma. 2023 Jan 30. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521185.","Rajkumar SV. Multiple myeloma: 2022 update on diagnosis, risk stratification, and management. Am J Hematol. 2022 Aug;97(8):1086-1107. doi: 10.1002/ajh.26590. Epub 2022 May 23. PMID: 35560063; PMCID: PMC9387011.","Yang W, Zheng J, Li R, Ren H, Hou B, Zhao Z, Wang D, Wang G, Liu J, Yan G, Wang D, Zhang X. Multiple myeloma with pathologically proven skull plasmacytoma after a mild head injury: Case report. Medicine (Baltimore). 2018 Sep;97(39):e12327. doi: 10.1097/MD.0000000000012327. PMID: 30278508; PMCID: PMC6181601.","Bitelman VM, Lopes JA, Nogueira AB, Frassetto FP, Duarte-Neto AN. \u0022Punched out\u0022 multiple myeloma lytic lesions in the skull. Autops Case Rep. 2016 Mar 30;6(1):7-9. doi: 10.4322/acr.2016.020. PMID: 27284535; PMCID: PMC4880428."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63668"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18028"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63668","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63668"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T10:33:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T10:33:34+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10742"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78256"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","posit